Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getIoFlowFlag(25.10)                                      getIoFlowFlag(25.10)

Name
       getIoFlowFlag - Gets the current I/O row flow flag setting

Syntax
       getIoFlowFlag

       [-help]

       Gets  the current I/O row flow flag setting.  A value of "0" means tra-
       ditional I/O flow where as a value of 1 means I/O row flow. To set  the
       I/O row flow flag, use the setIoFlowFlagcommand.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a brief description of the getIoFlowFlag command. For a
              detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man getIoFlowFlag

Example
              * The following command displays the current I/O row  flow  flag
                settings:

                getIoFlowFlag

Related Information
